  "prompt": "What are some useful websites for students?",
  "response": "There are numerous websites that cater to students' needs, whether it's for studying, research, productivity, or skill development. Here are some useful websites across various categories:\n\n### Educational Resources\n1. **Khan Academy** \u2013 Offers free courses on a wide range of subjects from mathematics to art history.\n2. **Coursera** \u2013 Provides online courses from universities and institutions around the world.\n3. **edX** \u2013 Offers free online classes from top universities like MIT and Harvard.\n4. **Duolingo** \u2013 A fun and interactive way to learn new languages.\n5. **Quizlet** \u2013 Provides study tools like flashcards and games to help you learn.\n\n### Research and Reference\n6. **Google Scholar** \u2013 A search engine for scholarly articles and academic papers.\n7. **JSTOR** \u2013 A digital library of academic journals, books, and primary sources.\n8. **PubMed** \u2013 A free resource for searching biomedical and life sciences literature.\n9. **Wolfram Alpha** \u2013 A computational knowledge engine that can solve complex math problems and provide data analysis.\n10. **Project Gutenberg** \u2013 Offers over 60,000 free eBooks, including many classics.\n\n### Productivity and Organization\n11. **Trello** \u2013 A project management tool that helps you organize tasks and projects visually.\n12. **Evernote** \u2013 A note-taking app that helps you keep track of your ideas, to-do lists, and research.\n13. **Google Drive** \u2013 Cloud storage for documents, presentations, and spreadsheets with collaborative features.\n14. **Notion** \u2013 An all-in-one workspace for notes, tasks, databases, and more.\n15. **Asana** \u2013 A tool for task and project management, ideal for group projects.\n\n### Writing and Citation\n16. **Grammarly** \u2013 An online writing assistant that checks your grammar and spelling.\n17. **Purdue OWL** \u2013 Provides resources for writing and citation, especially for MLA and APA styles.\n18. **EasyBib** \u2013 A citation generator that helps you create bibliographies quickly.\n\n### Skill Development\n19. **Codecademy** \u2013 Offers interactive coding lessons in various programming languages.\n20. **LinkedIn Learning** \u2013 Provides courses on business, technology, and creative skills.\n21. **Skillshare** \u2013 Offers thousands of classes on creative skills like photography, design, and writing.\n\n### Miscellaneous\n22. **TED Talks** \u2013 Inspirational and educational talks by experts in various fields.\n23. **SparkNotes** \u2013 Study guides and book summaries for literature and other subjects.\n24. **Chegg** \u2013 Offers textbook rentals, online tutoring, and homework help.\n25. **GoConqr** \u2013 A platform for creating and sharing study resources like mind maps, flashcards, and quizzes.\n\nThese websites can significantly enhance your academic experience, help you stay organized, and develop new skills.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
